<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-06-25T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-06-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="117" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d117">
                                <note rend="inline" type="source">462.00R296/4120</note>
                                <head><hi rend="italic">The Austrian Minister</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Prochnik</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                            State</gloss></hi></head>
                                <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-06-25">June 25,
                                            1931</date>.</dateline>
                                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 120/R</seg></opener>
                                <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Excellency</hi>: Confirming my oral
                                    statement made on Monday, June 22nd to the Undersecretary, Mr.
                                        Castle,<note n="57" xml:id="d117fn57">Memorandum of
                                        conversation not printed.</note> I have the honor to renew
                                    to Your Excellency the assurance that the Federal Government of
                                    the Republic of Austria is greatly pleased to unconditionally
                                    accept the proposal of the President of the United States in
                                    regard to debts and reparations.<note n="58" xml:id="d117fn58">For text of President Hoover’s proposal, see telegram No.
                                        262, June 20, 8 p.m., to the Ambassador in France, <ref target="#pg_33">p. 33</ref>.</note></p>
                                <p>Accept [etc.]</p>
                                <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Edgar
                                    Prochnik</hi></signed></closer>
                            </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>